            {
                "comment": "Professor Yin teaching 320 online was probably the worst experience of my undergrad career. There were 10 min quizzes every Friday morning where the average was almost always failing and the 2 hour discussions were about as pointless as you can get. I ended up dropping out of Engineering thanks to this class which could be a blessing or not idk yet",
                "difficulty_rating": 4,
                "quality_rating": 1
            },
            {
                "comment": "Prof. Yin is one of the best professors at UW. He is a very clear lecturer, is one of the smartest professors I know, and explains things very well. Not only is he a great lecturer, but he honestly cares about his students. In CBE 470, he made sure to have lunch with each student and is always available for help if you need it.",
                "difficulty_rating": 2,
                "quality_rating": 5
